Gluon and ghost condensates of dimension two and their relevance for
Yang-Mills theories are briefly reviewed.



The gauge condensate   in the
Landau gauge  

Motivation 

We shall consider pure Euclidean  Yang-Mills  



 In the last few years lattice simulationsof the two and three point functions of  Yang-Mills in the
Landau gauge have reported the existence of a large discrepancy
between the expected perturbative behavior and the lattice
results. The discrepancy is sizeable up to energies 
